This paper deals with the problem of finding a perfect matching in a regular bipartite graph, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also involves algorithms and computational complexity (cs.DS, cs.CC), as it discusses the running time of various algorithms for solving the problem. The paper also involves graph theory (cs.GT) and information theory (cs.IT), as it uses techniques from these fields to prove a uniform sampling theorem.
